author: Mark Molloy
title: Massive alligator 'Humpback' strolls past stunned tourists in Florida park
text:
Massive alligator 'Humpback' strolls past stunned tourists in Florida park Watch | Massive alligator strolls past stunned tourists in Florida park 00:30 Mark Molloy 17 January 2017 • 10:08am 
A massive alligator encounter stunned tourists at a Florida nature reserve, with online commentators joking it was “like a scene out of Jurassic Park”. 
Footage of the enormous gator nicknamed Humpback was captured at the Circle B Bar Reserve in Polk County, Florida. 
I t was shared on Facebook with the caption: “Nature at its best” and has been shared by more than 30,000 users on the social network. 
Kim Joiner, who captured the astonishing footage, admitted she was “a little” nervous as the alligator walked past just a few metres from stunned wildlife fans. 
“However I saw it coming,” she responded on Facebook. “I have been more scared when they just cross with no warning on Alligator Ally trail.” 
Responding to suggestions the footage was fake, Ms Joiner replied: “No photoshop. He was the biggest gator I have seen out there. I have been going out there for years too.” The huge 'Humpback' alligator was spotted at Circle B Bar Reserve in Florida Credit: Facebook / Kim Joiner 
M any commentators pointed out the huge gator looked like a dinosaur: 
“OMG!!! Looks like a dinosaur!!” wrote MJ Boughton. 
Another commented: “Holy cow, cannot believe those people are so close.” 
“Living in Florida is like a scene out of Jurassic Park,” one user joked. 
Patricia Wood Shannon added: “Holy smokes that is a dinosaur!” 
A woman who went to the reserve after seeing the footage told an ABC Action News reporter: “I thought it was fake. 
“I thought this has got to be fake. But then when I saw where it was and recognised the trail I said that has got to be real.”
